&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Guy’s &amp; St Thomas Community Tuberculosis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Community TB Team LSL (CTT LSL) is a multi-disciplinary team, which provides high quality services to TB patients and their families across Lambeth, Southwark and Lewisham.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;All Team members contribute to a comprehensive service, which includes clinical services, training, TB screening and treatment, outreach, quality improvement and developmental project work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide services from different sites within the Trust and with colleagues from Adults and Paediatrics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will also work at Evelina London Children’s Hospital where services are provided for children and young adults.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will need to be flexible with managing their work load across both hospitals and be a good team player with the right attitude for promoting good quality service delivery and patient’s satisfaction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position offers the opportunity for a highly motivated, dedicated and experienced nurse, sound professional and clinical knowledge which provides comprehensive tuberculosis services in different care settings to a diverse population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be educated to a degree level RGN with substantial experience in managing children and families with or suspected TB, possess relevant specialist TB Nursing qualifications, excellent communication skills; demonstrable experience of clinical leadership; ability to assess, plan, implement and evaluate health care in ensuring the delivery of high quality patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will work in line with the Trust Values and Behaviours framework&lt;br /&gt;Guys &amp; St Thomas’ Community Services is committed to staff development to ensure continuous professional development to maintain safe levels of competencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The vacant post is based at St Thomas hospital TB team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 15th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date :26th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
